article.headline: Temple 53, Dayton 51
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- Mardy Collins had 16 points and scored on a last-second layup to give Temple a 53-51 win over Dayton on Wednesday night. Temple (9-6, 3-2 Atlantic 10) went into the second half with a 24-21 lead and didn't give the Flyers another lead. Dayton (8-10, 0-4) tied it at 46 with 1:50 left, and Temple answered with a 3-pointer from Antywane Robinson, who had 12 points. Brian Roberts, who had 14 points for the Flyers, tied it again at 51 with a 22-foot 3-pointer with 13 seconds remaining. Collins then scored under double coverage with .9 left. Dustin Salisbery had 16 points for Temple. Monty Scott had 16 points for Dayton, and Norman Plummer added 10. Temple scored 15 points off of Dayton turnovers.
